WEBVTT

00:00:04.660 --> 00:00:06.450
Rukako.

00:00:06.450 --> 00:00:08.790
Stay calm and hear what I have to say.

00:00:08.790 --> 00:00:12.750
The truth is, you really used to be a guy.

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:22.290
Again with that?

00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:24.120
Wait! Don't cry!

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:26.660
Just stay calm and hear me out!

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:29.160
This is all for Mayuri's sake.

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:33.250
I need you to go back to being a guy.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:52.410
suu juuoku mono kodou no kazu sae

00:00:52.410 --> 00:00:59.080
anata ni wa matataki teido no saji na toukyuu

00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:04.330
kako ni torawarete mirai o nageku mo

00:01:04.330 --> 00:01:10.250
chiri hitotsu gosan o yurusanu hitsuzen

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:16.370
mugen ni hirogaru yume mo egaku mirai mo

00:01:16.370 --> 00:01:22.200
bokutachi ni yurusareta kyoei no kenri

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:28.410
yuugen sore wa futatsu no hari ga shimesu

00:01:28.410 --> 00:01:33.000
zankoku na yakujou to sentaku e

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.250
Hacking to the Gate

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:42.160
da kara ima ichi byou
goto ni sekaisen o koete

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:47.120
kimi no sono egao mamoritai no sa

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:54.120
soshite mata kanashimi
no nai jikan no ruupu e to

00:01:54.120 --> 00:02:00.790
nomi komarete yuku kodoku no kansokusha

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:20.580
What's with you?

00:02:20.580 --> 00:02:23.660
You look like you messed
up making yakisoba noodles

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:25.660
and tossed them all into the sink.

00:02:25.660 --> 00:02:30.580
"You look like you worked hard to
fill up your store discount stamp card

00:02:30.580 --> 00:02:33.330
but then it expired just
before you redeemed it."

00:02:33.330 --> 00:02:36.500
...Is what I'd prefer.

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:40.040
Looks like you still have
enough in you to joke around.

00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:41.160
Okarin!

00:02:41.160 --> 00:02:43.750
Mayushii is disappointed in you!

00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:45.330
Wh-What are you talking about?!

00:02:45.330 --> 00:02:47.500
Don't pretend you don't know!

00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:49.620
You made Ruka-chan cry!

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:50.660
H-How did you find out?!

00:02:50.660 --> 00:02:55.120
She suddenly burst into tears
when I invited her to the lab!

00:02:55.120 --> 00:03:01.040
When I asked what was wrong,
she said you called her a boy!

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:02.910
Did she tell you about the D-mail too?!

00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:04.700
D-mail?

00:03:04.700 --> 00:03:07.080
Don't try to talk your way out of this!

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:11.250
You should apologize to Ruka-chan!

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:14.790
Okabe!

00:03:15.870 --> 00:03:18.620
Did you really say something so mean to her?!

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:19.910
W-Wait! It's not what you think!

00:03:19.910 --> 00:03:23.160
-I have a reason for...!
-Like what?!

00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:24.660
Come with me, Assistant!

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:26.250
-Huh?!
-Just come!

00:03:26.250 --> 00:03:28.700
H-Hey! What are you doing?!

00:03:31.700 --> 00:03:35.290
So the next D-mail I have to undo

00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:39.910
is the one we sent to Rukako's
mother's pager before Rukako was born.

00:03:39.910 --> 00:03:43.830
Urushibara-san is actually a boy...?

00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:45.620
That's unbelievable.

00:03:45.620 --> 00:03:49.250
But it's the truth... was the truth.

00:03:49.250 --> 00:03:52.540
Her, a guy...

00:03:52.540 --> 00:03:55.580
A guy like Hashida?

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.330
Now that would be bad...

00:04:04.330 --> 00:04:06.910
No, he still looks exactly the same.

00:04:06.910 --> 00:04:08.450
That's acceptable, then.

00:04:08.450 --> 00:04:11.450
At any rate, we have to
turn Rukako back into a guy

00:04:11.450 --> 00:04:13.160
if we want to save Mayuri!

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:19.410
But this time you
know what her D-mail said.

00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:24.250
Can't you just quietly undo it without
discussing the situation with her?

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:28.410
I don't know her mother's pager number.

00:04:28.410 --> 00:04:32.700
Besides, I feel it would be more
responsible to tell her the truth

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:34.870
rather than resort to cheap trickery.

00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:38.250
And that "responsibility" wound
up making her cry, remember?

00:04:38.250 --> 00:04:41.790
You're just playing around as usual, right?

00:04:41.790 --> 00:04:44.750
You're just joking, right?

00:04:44.750 --> 00:04:46.330
That's so mean!

00:04:46.330 --> 00:04:49.830
I can't believe you'd say such things to me...!

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:54.290
I think you jinxed things for her.

00:04:54.290 --> 00:04:55.580
Jinxed?

00:04:55.580 --> 00:04:57.580
It's not like I said anything like,

00:04:57.580 --> 00:05:01.000
"Once this battle is over, I'm getting married."

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.250
That's a jinx that ends in death.
I'm talking about love here.

00:05:05.250 --> 00:05:06.500
Love?!

00:05:06.500 --> 00:05:10.790
Yeah. Hearing her beloved
Okabe say, "You're a dude,"

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.830
has broken her tender heart.

00:05:13.830 --> 00:05:16.580
B-But Rukako is a guy!

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:20.200
In a previous world line, maybe.

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:23.950
"Rukako: (No subject)"
"Assistant: ( ﾟДﾟ)"

00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:25.370
"Okabe-san I have something important to discuss.
Could you come to the shrine? I'll be waiting."

00:05:25.370 --> 00:05:27.660
"I have something important to discuss.

00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:30.790
Could you come to the shrine?"

00:05:32.950 --> 00:05:34.580
Okabe-san.

00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:36.500
Sorry about earlier.

00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:40.200
No, I'm sorry for bursting into tears...

00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:43.040
So, you had something important to discuss?

00:05:43.040 --> 00:05:46.750
Yes. I have a favor to ask...

00:05:46.750 --> 00:05:47.950
A favor?

00:05:47.950 --> 00:05:51.370
I believe what you said.

00:05:51.370 --> 00:05:53.750
So, umm...

00:05:55.500 --> 00:05:57.950
In exchange for turning back into a boy...

00:05:57.950 --> 00:06:03.540
...I-I ask that you be my boyfriend!

00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:06.290
Boyfriend?!

00:06:06.290 --> 00:06:09.000
Wh-Why me?!

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:11.370
Because I like you.

00:06:11.370 --> 00:06:14.660
Because I like you, Okabe-san!

00:06:14.660 --> 00:06:18.450
So, tomorrow, for just one day...

00:06:18.450 --> 00:06:21.200
...please be my boyfriend!

00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:25.540
B-But, you're a guy--

00:06:27.790 --> 00:06:30.750
Okay! I'll do it! Just don't cry!

00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:34.580
Very well! If it's just for tomorrow,
then I'll be your boyfriend!

00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:37.330
R-Really?!

00:06:37.330 --> 00:06:38.580
Why are you crying?!

00:06:38.580 --> 00:06:41.620
I can't help it, I'm just so happy...!

00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:45.950
That was actually kind of touching...

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:50.950
So now you're going on a date
with Urushibara-san tomorrow?

00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:53.200
Yes.

00:06:53.200 --> 00:06:57.370
A mad scientist, going on a
date with a high school girl?

00:06:57.370 --> 00:06:58.290
Get off my back!

00:06:58.290 --> 00:07:03.660
I'm swallowing my pride and asking
my lowly assistant for dating advice!

00:07:03.660 --> 00:07:05.450
I told you, I'm not your assistant!

00:07:05.450 --> 00:07:08.450
Oh? You're going on a
date with someone, Kyouma?

00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:13.120
I brought your order! Two ice coffees!

00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:15.580
Who's the date with? Mayushii?

00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:17.700
Or... maybe this girl?

00:07:17.700 --> 00:07:20.580
No, this is my assistant.

00:07:20.580 --> 00:07:22.790
I know you're trying to master
your special technique and all,

00:07:22.790 --> 00:07:26.500
but you chase way too many girls, meow!

00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:30.830
Oh? Way too many girls, huh?

00:07:30.830 --> 00:07:35.250
Hey! Don't just spout misleading
statements and then leave!

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:42.910
Say. Would you, umm...

00:07:42.910 --> 00:07:46.040
Would you do anything to
master your special technique?

00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:47.450
Huh?

00:07:47.450 --> 00:07:51.700
No, err, I mean, would Hououin
Kyouma do anything for it?!

00:07:51.700 --> 00:07:54.580
Why are you talking about that too?

00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:58.330
-I don't get you.
-I-I'm just asking!

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:02.370
I was wondering if he'd do whatever
it takes to master that technique

00:08:02.370 --> 00:08:05.040
if there was someone he already loved...

00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:07.910
-There's no meaning behind it, though!
-Why are you getting mad?!

00:08:07.910 --> 00:08:09.410
I'm not mad!

00:08:09.410 --> 00:08:11.700
Anyway, if that's how your character is,

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:13.830
then just go on a date with Urushibara-san!

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:16.620
I already told you I plan to!

00:08:16.620 --> 00:08:19.450
Okarin...

00:08:19.450 --> 00:08:24.040
Can you fill me in on all the juicy details too?

00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:25.620
"CRT Workshop"

00:08:25.620 --> 00:08:28.080
If you want dating advice, I'm your man!

00:08:28.080 --> 00:08:32.410
I've had happy kissy time with dozens of girls!

00:08:32.410 --> 00:08:36.500
Nene-chan, Shiori-chan,
Honoka-chan, Rinko-chan...

00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:39.410
Those are all game characters.

00:08:39.410 --> 00:08:42.830
This is a real-life date.

00:08:42.830 --> 00:08:48.410
Somewhere popular, like Aoyama,
Omotesandou, or Nishi-Azabu...

00:08:48.410 --> 00:08:50.700
"Fashionable and trendy..."

00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:52.620
"Premium night..."

00:08:52.620 --> 00:08:55.200
"Special dinner..."

00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:58.000
It's no good. This stuff's a world all its own.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:01.370
A world not part of reality.

00:09:01.370 --> 00:09:03.830
But one you still have to accept.

00:09:03.830 --> 00:09:06.660
I'll have you know that
the great Hououin Kyouma,

00:09:06.660 --> 00:09:11.700
with his 170 IQ--which is the same
as Isaac Newton's, I might add--

00:09:11.700 --> 00:09:14.040
finds research more interesting than girls--

00:09:14.040 --> 00:09:19.040
You're clearly a virgin. Thank you very much.

00:09:19.040 --> 00:09:21.330
What about you, then?!

00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:26.080
Do you really have that much
dating experience under your belt?!

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:27.120
See!

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.450
You're so absorbed in
your studying and research

00:09:29.450 --> 00:09:31.750
that you have zero experience in such things!

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:34.830
Your adolescence was clearly a lonely one!

00:09:34.830 --> 00:09:37.500
Shut up! So what if I'm a virgin?!

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:48.080
"The key to a first date is making
the best impression possible."

00:09:48.080 --> 00:09:53.250
"Clothing-wise, brand names are
unnecessary; a sense of cleanliness is--"

00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:55.450
Sounds like I'm A-OK in that department.

00:09:55.450 --> 00:09:57.370
Nothing says "clean" like a lab coat.

00:09:57.370 --> 00:09:59.500
No one wears lab coats on dates.

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:01.950
"The same holds true
when choosing where to dine."

00:10:01.950 --> 00:10:05.290
"Don't feel compelled to select
an overly-expensive restaurant."

00:10:05.290 --> 00:10:08.200
"Any place you visit regularly will suffice."

00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:10.000
Regularly...?

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.160
-This place is out of the question.
-Obviously!

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:16.620
Who would have a date
in a place this savage?!

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:19.200
Then that just leaves...

00:10:19.200 --> 00:10:20.450
...May Queen.

00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:23.580
Huh?! A maid café on your first date?!

00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:26.200
-An old weapon shop.
-Weapon-shopping on a date?!

00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:29.410
You're just reading straight
from a dating manual!

00:10:29.410 --> 00:10:33.330
Quit acting so high and
mighty, you American virgin!

00:10:33.330 --> 00:10:36.160
-Who are you calling an American virgin?!
-Who else but you?!

00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:38.160
Yes! I'm a virgin! The end!

00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:42.040
Uhh, maybe you'd prefer
this instead of that lousy book?

00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:45.200
-That's a hentai game strategy guide!
-So?!

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:47.910
They have dates in hentai games!

00:10:47.910 --> 00:10:50.410
Holding hands and stuff
is totally erotic, y'know?!

00:10:50.410 --> 00:10:53.290
Walking arm in arm, with
your elbow touching her boob...

00:10:53.290 --> 00:10:55.250
That's totally hot!

00:10:55.250 --> 00:11:00.160
And then you kiss and embrace
at the end of the date! Hot damn!

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.790
Screw you real-lifers!

00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:09.580
It's already morning
and I still don't got a plan...

00:11:09.580 --> 00:11:13.040
Quit your grumbling and put it on!

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:14.700
Geez, take off the tags!

00:11:14.700 --> 00:11:17.450
That's no way to tie a necktie!
You're unbelievable!

00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:20.540
Sheesh! You're a lost cause!

00:11:20.540 --> 00:11:21.500
There!

00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:24.290
I feel like I'm wearing a leash now...

00:11:24.290 --> 00:11:26.580
Here's a handkerchief.

00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:28.500
Do you know how to use it?

00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:32.410
Doesn't this one mean, "I'm waiting
for you, even after all this time?"

00:11:32.410 --> 00:11:34.830
That's the yellow kind.

00:11:34.830 --> 00:11:38.660
How do you even know
obscure trivia like that? That's old.

00:11:38.660 --> 00:11:41.250
You know it too, though.

00:11:41.250 --> 00:11:42.450
S-So?!

00:11:42.450 --> 00:11:47.450
You're actually supposed to spread
it out when a girl sits on a park bench.

00:11:47.450 --> 00:11:48.660
Whatever.

00:11:48.660 --> 00:11:52.910
I'll covertly follow you and text
you advice if anything comes up.

00:11:52.910 --> 00:11:56.750
-You're going to follow us?!
-Yeah, Hashida too.

00:11:56.750 --> 00:11:58.040
Huh?!

00:11:58.040 --> 00:12:01.750
Commence Operation Valkyrie!

00:12:01.750 --> 00:12:04.000
Why Norse mythology?

00:12:04.790 --> 00:12:07.660
"When meeting your date,
time is of the utmost importance.

00:12:07.660 --> 00:12:11.540
Be sure to arrive at least 15 minutes early."

00:12:15.040 --> 00:12:17.040
Okabe-san!

00:12:17.040 --> 00:12:18.910
I'm sorry!

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:23.000
I thought I had left early...

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:25.120
Have you been waiting long?

00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:30.160
Oh, no... I, uhh, just got here too...

00:12:30.160 --> 00:12:32.250
That's a relief.

00:12:33.910 --> 00:12:36.870
Sh-Shall we go?

00:12:36.870 --> 00:12:38.830
Yes!

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:50.040
I've never seen you
without a lab coat before!

00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:54.080
W-Well, it is a date and all...

00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:55.660
"When walking with a girl,

00:12:55.660 --> 00:12:57.950
subtly take the side with oncoming traffic!"

00:12:57.950 --> 00:12:59.660
Is something the matter?

00:12:59.660 --> 00:13:02.950
Oh, no, it's nothing...!

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:05.120
Whoa! What's that?!

00:13:05.120 --> 00:13:07.160
That's not subtle in the least...

00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:12.080
"And casually guard her from
any passing cars and motorcycles!"

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:14.870
-Whoa!
-Did he guard her?!

00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:16.160
Okabe-san?!

00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:18.830
-Oww...
-Are you all right?

00:13:18.830 --> 00:13:21.250
Wait, he just tripped?!

00:13:21.250 --> 00:13:26.200
On top of that, a maid had to help
him up?! And he took her tissue pack?!

00:13:26.200 --> 00:13:29.450
Miss Makise. Is it me or are you on edge?

00:13:33.290 --> 00:13:36.120
Th-The weather is nice today.

00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:39.000
Y-Yeah.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:40.830
But there are clouds, too.

00:13:40.830 --> 00:13:42.450
Yes.

00:13:48.040 --> 00:13:50.950
This cake tastes very good.

00:13:50.950 --> 00:13:54.200
Yes. The coffee, too.

00:13:57.580 --> 00:13:58.870
Why?!

00:13:58.870 --> 00:14:01.620
I could hold a normal
conversation just fine before,

00:14:01.620 --> 00:14:03.290
but as soon as it turned into a date...!

00:14:03.290 --> 00:14:05.370
This is a wonderful place!

00:14:05.370 --> 00:14:08.330
-Do you come here often?
-No...!

00:14:08.330 --> 00:14:10.540
This is going terribly!

00:14:10.540 --> 00:14:13.370
"The key is to play 'conversation catch'!"

00:14:13.370 --> 00:14:17.040
T-Today is actually my first time...

00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:18.120
He tossed it back!

00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:21.250
Speaking of firsts, today is August 14th,

00:14:21.250 --> 00:14:25.370
the anniversary of the very
first patent issued in Japan!

00:14:25.370 --> 00:14:27.250
Tossed it back where?!

00:14:27.250 --> 00:14:30.700
You certainly are knowledgeable, Okabe-san!

00:14:30.700 --> 00:14:32.660
W-Well, you know how it is...

00:14:37.330 --> 00:14:39.580
Can we go now, Miss Makise?

00:14:39.580 --> 00:14:43.500
We're no help at all;
we're just sitting here watching.

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:46.410
No. We have to see it through to the end.

00:14:46.410 --> 00:14:48.620
Thank you for coming!

00:14:50.580 --> 00:14:52.080
Umm...

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:57.120
Do you find it boring after all?
Going on a date with me...

00:14:57.120 --> 00:14:58.580
Wha...?! D-Don't be silly!

00:14:58.580 --> 00:15:02.750
Next is a nice walk around town! Come along!

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:07.290
Ruka-chan?

00:15:07.290 --> 00:15:08.910
It's so hot...

00:15:12.580 --> 00:15:16.450
He just walked straight to Ueno and back...!

00:15:21.160 --> 00:15:23.700
Okabe-san.

00:15:23.700 --> 00:15:28.540
Do you remember when we first met?

00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:33.660
A bunch of men with cameras
suddenly overwhelmed me,

00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:38.330
but then you showed up
to save the day, remember?

00:15:38.330 --> 00:15:40.000
Yeah...

00:15:43.160 --> 00:15:46.200
Th-Thank you!

00:15:46.200 --> 00:15:48.870
I'm sorry, though...

00:15:48.870 --> 00:15:50.450
What are you apologizing for?

00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:56.160
For, well, being a boy
even though I look this way...!

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:03.370
It makes no difference
whether you're a boy or a girl!

00:16:03.370 --> 00:16:06.290
None of that matters!

00:16:06.290 --> 00:16:11.910
Those words you spoke made me so happy!

00:16:11.910 --> 00:16:17.000
Those words are what made me like you!

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:20.950
"None of that matters," huh...

00:16:20.950 --> 00:16:22.620
W-Wait a second!

00:16:22.620 --> 00:16:25.910
Isn't that memory from when you were a guy?!

00:16:25.910 --> 00:16:27.870
Huh? What?

00:16:27.870 --> 00:16:30.950
What... What am I saying?

00:16:30.950 --> 00:16:33.660
I'm feeling confused...

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:36.700
It's just like what happened with Faris...

00:16:36.700 --> 00:16:39.660
She's regaining memories
from an earlier world line...

00:16:43.250 --> 00:16:47.700
Thank you for today.

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:53.120
Being my boyfriend made me so very...

00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.830
So very happy!

00:16:55.830 --> 00:16:56.790
H-Hey, now!

00:16:56.790 --> 00:17:00.500
This is my mother's pager number.

00:17:10.160 --> 00:17:14.620
"Meat meat veggies veggies
meat meat veggies veggies..."

00:17:14.620 --> 00:17:17.620
This should make Urushibara-san's mom think

00:17:17.620 --> 00:17:21.660
that the previous message was just a prank.

00:17:21.660 --> 00:17:23.790
We're all set!

00:17:25.410 --> 00:17:27.580
What's wrong, Okabe?

00:17:27.580 --> 00:17:29.000
Too-too-roo!

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:30.790
Guess what, guess what?!

00:17:30.790 --> 00:17:35.950
Mayushii saw Ruka-chan out
on a date with someone earlier!

00:17:35.950 --> 00:17:38.160
Oh, that was Okarin.

00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:40.290
Huh? No way!

00:17:40.290 --> 00:17:43.160
That definitely wasn't Okarin!

00:17:43.160 --> 00:17:47.950
He was wearing regular clothes
and seemed like a real gentleman!

00:17:47.950 --> 00:17:49.540
Exactly!

00:17:49.540 --> 00:17:51.160
That wasn't me!

00:17:51.160 --> 00:17:55.000
Ruka didn't have a date with the real me!

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:56.910
Okarin?

00:17:59.040 --> 00:18:01.410
O-Our date isn't over yet!

00:18:01.410 --> 00:18:03.450
Huh? But, Okabe-san...!

00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:06.700
It's "Kyouma"! Have you
forgotten my name, Rukako?!

00:18:06.700 --> 00:18:10.200
All that male, female,
boyfriend, girlfriend stuff...!

00:18:10.200 --> 00:18:13.540
I was the one who was confused!

00:18:13.540 --> 00:18:16.410
None of that matters!

00:18:16.410 --> 00:18:22.080
I've finally realized that I'm me and you're you:

00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:23.660
Rukako, my pupil!

00:18:27.410 --> 00:18:29.250
Right!

00:18:29.250 --> 00:18:32.040
Good! Then go get the
Supernatural Sword Samidare!

00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:33.040
"Yanabayashi Shrine"

00:18:33.040 --> 00:18:34.290
That's it!

00:18:34.290 --> 00:18:35.700
Keep it up!

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:37.750
Right!

00:18:37.750 --> 00:18:40.580
Now listen well, Rukako.

00:18:40.580 --> 00:18:44.080
The legends surrounding
this supernatural sword

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:46.580
can be traced back to the time of Yoshitsune.

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:49.870
On a night of a crimson full moon,

00:18:49.870 --> 00:18:50.950
-a wandering samurai lost his way...

00:18:50.950 --> 00:18:53.200
-Welp, there he goes...
-a wandering samurai lost his way...

00:18:53.200 --> 00:18:57.910
That's wonderful!
He's made up with Ruka-chan!

00:18:57.910 --> 00:19:01.080
Looks like we aren't needed anymore.

00:19:05.080 --> 00:19:10.160
Please help Mayuri-chan.

00:19:10.160 --> 00:19:13.540
The old computer you're looking for...

00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:15.620
The IBN 5100?!

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:21.950
It was in our storehouse
until last New Year's Day.

00:19:21.950 --> 00:19:27.750
But I accidentally broke it,
while I was cleaning the storehouse...

00:19:27.750 --> 00:19:30.370
So it's my fault!

00:19:30.370 --> 00:19:33.250
Please, Okabe-san!

00:19:33.250 --> 00:19:37.200
Please save Mayuri-chan!

00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:42.160
I'm really glad I was able to train
with you again. It's been so long.

00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:46.580
-Ruka--
-Please go now.

00:19:46.580 --> 00:19:50.120
Before I start crying...

00:19:53.410 --> 00:19:57.160
This is the perfect time
for that secret phrase, isn't it?

00:19:57.160 --> 00:20:00.580
El Psy Congree...

00:20:00.580 --> 00:20:03.700
Congroo.

00:20:03.700 --> 00:20:06.500
El Psy...

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:12.450
Honestly, I don't want to turn back.

00:20:12.450 --> 00:20:13.700
If I...

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:16.750
If I go back to being a boy,

00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:21.200
I'll have to seal away my feelings for you!

00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:26.950
As a boy, I won't be
allowed to like you...!

00:20:26.950 --> 00:20:28.370
Rukako...

00:20:28.370 --> 00:20:33.450
And if I go back to being a boy,
I'll forget today ever happened, won't I?

00:20:33.450 --> 00:20:39.660
I'll forget we went on a date,
that we trained together again...

00:20:39.660 --> 00:20:44.330
That I could touch you the way I am now...

00:20:44.330 --> 00:20:49.080
If being a girl means I have
to go through this much pain,

00:20:49.080 --> 00:20:51.830
then I should never
have wished to be one!

00:20:51.830 --> 00:20:57.450
You'll always be Rukako to me, even as a boy!

00:20:57.450 --> 00:20:59.700
Nothing will change!

00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:01.500
You're right.

00:21:01.500 --> 00:21:03.790
It's like you said,
whether I'm a boy or a girl...

00:21:03.790 --> 00:21:07.370
"None of that matters!"

00:21:07.370 --> 00:21:10.250
Still, all I ask...

00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:16.080
Is that you remember me
when I used to be a girl...!

00:21:16.080 --> 00:21:19.120
I will. I'll never forget.

00:21:19.120 --> 00:21:20.540
Never.

00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:30.250
What's the matter, Okabe-san?

00:21:32.620 --> 00:21:33.830
Urushibara Ruka.

00:21:33.830 --> 00:21:36.290
The voice and mannerisms of a woman...

00:21:36.290 --> 00:21:40.250
No, even more feminine than a woman.

00:21:40.250 --> 00:21:42.040
Tell me, Rukako...

00:21:42.040 --> 00:21:43.160
Yes?

00:21:43.160 --> 00:21:45.580
Do you... like me?

00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:47.700
Wh-What brought that on?!

00:21:47.700 --> 00:21:48.950
Do you?

00:21:48.950 --> 00:21:51.290
Umm, err...

00:21:51.290 --> 00:21:54.450
I respect you!

00:21:54.450 --> 00:21:57.540
But... he's a dude.

00:22:06.080 --> 00:22:09.950
That just leaves one more D-mail...

00:22:20.700 --> 00:22:23.830
kisei sareta

00:22:23.830 --> 00:22:29.660
shikai mujihi naru

00:22:29.660 --> 00:22:32.700
juuni no

00:22:32.700 --> 00:22:37.410
shihai nogarerarenai

00:22:37.410 --> 00:22:41.370
ansoku no

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:46.290
asu o negatta

00:22:46.290 --> 00:22:50.450
te no naka no

00:22:50.450 --> 00:22:54.950
toutoi jishou no chihei e

00:22:54.950 --> 00:22:59.200
torawareshi meiyaku

00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:03.500
arawareta gishou no rinkaku

00:23:03.500 --> 00:23:07.750
seimei no tenchi wa

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:12.750
moumoku na jikan o kizanda

00:23:12.750 --> 00:23:18.080
habatake batafurai kiseki no batafurai

00:23:18.080 --> 00:23:21.620
anata e sasagu

00:23:21.620 --> 00:23:25.950
namida no batafurai mabushii batafurai

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:28.790
subete ga

00:23:28.790 --> 00:23:33.700
ima kakikaerareru

